<h2>
  Value Constraints
</h2>

<p>
  The constraints in this section apply to the values passed directly to helpers:
</p>

<ul>
  <li>
    <code>
      \{{liquid-bind}}
    </code>
    match against its own bound contexts.
  </li>
  <li>
    <code>
      \{{liquid-if}}
    </code>
    matches against its predicate.
  </li>
</ul>

<p>
  These are the three value constraint methods:
</p>

<dl class="dl-horizontal">
  <dt>
    fromValue
  </dt>
  <dd>
    Matches the value before it changes.
  </dd>
  <dt>
    toValue
  </dt>
  <dd>
    Matches the value after it changes.
  </dd>
  <dt>
    betweenValues
  </dt>
  <dd>
    Matches the value both before and after a change.
  </dd>
</dl>

<p>
  Each one accepts a single argument that can be:
</p>

<ul>
  <li>
    A function that tests the value and returns true if the
  constraint matches.
  </li>

  <li>
    A regular expression that will be matched against the
    value.
  </li>

  <li>
    A boolean, which will cause the constraint to match any value
    that is correspondingly truthy or falsy.
  </li>

  <li>
    A string or number, which will match exactly.
  </li>

  <li>
    <code>
      null
    </code>
    , which will match
    <code>
      null
    </code>
    or
    <code>
      undefined
    </code>
  </li>
</ul>

